== Naishi of Itsukushima Shrine == At [[:en:Itsukushima Shrine|Itsukushima Shrine]], the Naishi were female shrine priests ([[:en:Miko|Miko]]). Their duties included participating in rituals, reciting {{ill|Imayō|ja|今様|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imayō|qq=}} to entertain noble guests who lodged at the shrine, and performing {{ill|bugaku|ja|舞楽|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/bugaku|qq=}}. According to the "Itsukushima Michishiba-ki" ({{ill|厳島道芝記|ja|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/厳島道芝記|qq=}}), the shrine maintained a hierarchical structure of Naishi from first Rank (一﨟) to eighth Rank (八﨟), collectively referred to as the "Yaotome" (八乙女) or "Hon-Naishi" (本内侍). Additional titles such as "Wagoto-Naishi" (和琴内侍) and "Karagami-Naishi" (韓神内侍) indicate a system of more than ten positions.
It is also said that {{ill|Mikohimegimi|ja|御子姫君|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikohimegimi|qq=}}, the seventh daughter of {{ill|Taira no Kiyomori|ja|Taira no Kiyomori|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Kiyomori|qq=}}, was born to Kiyomori and a Naishi of Itsukushima Shrine during his tenure as the governor of Aki Province.
